<HL>
   NBD Bancorp Acquires Assets
</HL>
<DATE>
06/05/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   NBD
</CO>
<IN>
SAVINGS AND LOANS, THRIFTS, CREDIT UNIONS (SAL)
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<GV>
FEDERAL GOVERNMENT (FDL)
</GV>
<LP>
   DETROIT -- NBD Bancorp said it assumed the deposits and
acquired some assets of First Venice Savings &amp; Loan
Association of Venice, Fla., from Resolution Trust Corp. NBD
said it will form NBD Bank, Federal Savings Bank, to complete
the deal.
   Resolution Trust is a federal agency created to sell off
failed thrifts seized by the government.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   First Venice has $57 million of deposits and NBD will
acquire $46 million of assets, which are primarily
residential mortgage loans. NBD Chairman Charles T. Fisher
III said the acquisition will help NBD deliver custom banking
services to NBD trust customers in Florida. "We do not intend
to become a major player in the savings and loan business,"
Mr. Fisher said.
</TEXT>
