</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   KGE
</CO>
<IN>
ELECTRIC UTILITIES (ELC)
</IN>
<LP>
   WICHITA, Kansas -- Kansas Gas &amp; Electric Co. said a ruling
by the Kansas Court of Appeals means the company won't have
to refund $8.7 million plus interest to its customers as
previously ordered.
   The utility said that the court ruled that a $29 million
annual rate increase granted by the Kansas Corporation
Commission effective January 1989 should have been permanent.
Earlier this year, the state commission rejected a staff
recommendation and ruled that part of the rate increase was
subject to refund. The commission at that time also ordered a
second $6.9 million refund that the company is still
appealing.
